          </div>
          <div>
            <p class="font-label text-primary font-bold text-sm mb-2">MEDIUM EQUIPMENT (Compressors, Pumps)</p>
            <p class="font-body text-on-surface text-sm">25–35mm honeycomb | Medium-weight machinery | Regional distribution</p>
          </div>
          <div>
            <p class="font-label text-primary font-bold text-sm mb-2">LARGE HVAC UNITS (Outdoor AC Units, Chillers)</p>
            <p class="font-body text-on-surface text-sm">40–50mm honeycomb | Heavy equipment | Long-distance shipping</p>
          </div>
          <div>
            <p class="font-label text-primary font-bold text-sm mb-2">SPECIALIZED EQUIPMENT (Custom Machinery)</p>
            <p class="font-body text-on-surface text-sm">50mm+ multi-layer | Extreme protection | International shipping</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <section class="mb-12">
        <h2 class="font-headline text-2xl font-bold text-on-surface mb-6">FAQs for Industrial HVAC Packaging</h2>
        <div class="space-y-4">
          <details class="group border border-outline-variant/20 rounded-lg p-4">
            <summary class="font-label font-bold text-on-surface cursor-pointer">How do I calculate honeycomb thickness needed for my equipment?</summary>
            <p class="font-body text-on-surface text-sm mt-3 leading-relaxed">Consider equipment weight, fragility, shipping distance, and handling risks. HVAC units typically need 25–50mm. Test your specific equipment with trial shipments or consult our Balakong team for recommendations.</p>
          </details>

          <details class="group border border-outline-variant/20 rounded-lg p-4">
            <summary class="font-label font-bold text-on-surface cursor-pointer">Can honeycomb withstand vibration from heavy truck transport?</summary>
            <p class="font-body text-on-surface text-sm mt-3 leading-relaxed">Yes, especially with multi-layer construction. Honeycomb absorbs vibration energy effectively. Pair with internal bracing and anti-vibration feet for maximum protection on long Malaysian highways.</p>
          </details>

          <details class="group border border-outline-variant/20 rounded-lg p-4">
            <summary class="font-label font-bold text-on-surface cursor-pointer">Is honeycomb stronger than wood crating for machinery?</summary>
            <p class="font-body text-on-surface text-sm mt-3 leading-relaxed">Honeycomb is lighter and more flexible while wood is rigid. For shock protection, honeycomb excels. For stacking and long-term storage, wood may be better. Many shippers use both in hybrid approaches.</p>
          </details>

          <details class="group border border-outline-variant/20 rounded-lg p-4">
            <summary class="font-label font-bold text-on-surface cursor-pointer">How do I protect copper piping and refrigerant lines?</summary>
            <p class="font-body text-on-surface text-sm mt-3 leading-relaxed">Wrap piping separately in foam tube insulation, then layer with honeycomb protection. Secure lines to prevent shifting. Use corner protectors on fragile connections.</p>
          </details>

          <details class="group border border-outline-variant/20 rounded-lg p-4">
            <summary class="font-label font-bold text-on-surface cursor-pointer">Where can I source industrial-grade honeycomb for HVAC shipping?</summary>
            <p class="font-body text-on-surface text-sm mt-3 leading-relaxed">Quinocycle supplies industrial-grade honeycomb in custom thicknesses for HVAC and machinery. Minimum order RM 1,000. Contact us for bulk industrial packaging solutions serving Balakong and all of Peninsular Malaysia.</p>
          </details>
        </div>
      </section>

